                <h1>Power Up Your App with Flutter Background Service</h1>
                <p>Flutter background service enables developers to run tasks in the background while the app is not actively in use. This is crucial for long-running processes like data collection, notifications, and audio playback. By using plugins like workmanager, developers can efficiently execute tasks even when the app is closed, ensuring seamless user experiences.</p>
